answers.body_markdown:
The exception you are getting, `OpenQA.Selenium.WebDriverTimeoutException`, occurs in your waiting method `NgWebDriver.WaitForAngular()`. This shows that the WebDriver is waiting for something to appear/be clickable/etc, but fails to do so before reaching the waiting time limit. 

Just by guessing from the structure and class names of your HTML, the element you are trying to click could be either of;

 - Inside/covered by another element, i.e. the i-element inside the button, or is the element you actually want to click beneath the i-element ?
 - The element is hidden, and since selenium is designed to fail such clicks, it fails to click this element.

I suggest that you experiment with clicking on the parent element, or see if there is another child element that you should click. If that fails, you could also try clicking with a JavascriptExecutor:

    public void ClickUsingJquery(string selector) {
        string script = String.Format(&quot;jQuery(\&quot;{0}\&quot;).click();&quot;, selector);
        TestContext.WriteLine(&quot;Script to execute: &quot; + script);
        var javaScriptExecutor = this.driver as IJavaScriptExecutor; 
        javaScriptExecutor?.ExecuteScript(script);
    }
(Replace `getElementById(&#39;{elementId}&#39;).click()` and the `selector` parameter with whatever way of selecting your element you prefer).

